lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2598  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Impairment of neuronal branching and spine formation in the primary cultured hippocampal neurons in DGKB KO mice.\nDGKB-induced branching and spine formation in the primary cultured hippocampal neurons.\nAbnormality of synapse density and phosphatidic acid/diacylglycerol levels in the hippocampus of DGKB KO mice.\n\n21/2/2018 Pim\nFig.5: \"Impairment of spine formation in the primary cultured hippocampal neurons from DGKβ KO mice.\"\nFig.6: \"DGKβ-induced branching and spine formation in the primary cultured hippocampal neurons from WT mice.\"\nFig.7: \"Rescue of impaired branching and spine formation in the primary cultured hippocampal neurons from KO mice by DGKβ overexpression\". Experimental description: Materials and Methods\nAnimals\nPregnant mice (day 14) (C57BL/6JJmsSlc) for the primary culture were obtained from Japan SLC Inc. (Hamamatsu, Japan). DGKβ KO mice were produced using the Sleeping Beauty transposon system.\n\nConstruction of plasmid encoding GFP-DGKβ and its splice variant form (C-cut mutant).\nThe cDNA encoding DGKβ was produced by a polymerase chain reaction (PCR) with cDNA for DGKβ as the template. The sense and anti-sense primers used were 5'-ATAGGATCCATGACAAACCAGGAAAAATGG-3' and 5'-ATAGGATCCTCATTCCTTGCTTCGGTTT-3'." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2598" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

dc:date  a      owl:AnnotationProperty .

